article.description: — Marcus Weathers scored 17 points and Kendric Davis scored 13 points and grabbed six rebounds and SMU beat South Florida 74-54 on Wednesday night for its fourth straight win.
article.headline: Weathers scores 17 to carry SMU over South Florida 74-54
article.linkText: Weathers scores 17 to carry SMU over South Florida 74-54
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. -- — Marcus Weathers scored 17 points and Kendric Davis scored 13 points and grabbed six rebounds and SMU beat South Florida 74-54 on Wednesday night for its fourth straight win. Emmanuel Bandoumel added 12 points for SMU (15-4, 6-1 American Athletic Conference) Caleb Murphy scored 14 points, Jamir Chaplin scored 11 and Javon Greene had 10 points and six rebounds for the Bulls (6-12, 1-5). SMU also defeated South Florida 77-65 on Jan. 12. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
